  "title": "SENIOR SITE ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>1. Minimum Bachelor degree with at least Six (6) years’ relevant field safety experience in supervision of installation and maintenance of roadside and Civil and structural coordination with government/utility agencies and other contractors.</p><p>2. Experience as a safety auditor/inspector in ensuring Environmental, Safety and Health practices are complied with.</p><p>3. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, resourceful and meticulous.</p><p>4. Highly motivated and pro-active with the ability to work both independently as well as in a team.</p><p>5. Proficient in Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint for Windows.</p><p>6. Good verbal communication and writing skills in English.</p><p>7. Be expected to travel regularly between office and sites.</p><p>8. Prepared to work on site and perform night work based on project needs.</p>",
